title: Wildcats start season with sweep
text:
Wildcats start season with sweep By: Uncredited Report Error 
The Westman Wildcats got off to a roaring start to the Manitoba Female Midget Hockey League season by sweeping the Norman Wild in Hartney. 
Ashton Bell scored twice on Sunday in the Wildcat’s 5-0 victory. Jaedon Cooke, Andrea Sanderson and McKenzie Meek added singles while Kaitlyn Slator stopped all 14 shots for the shutout. 
On Saturday, Camryn Clyne scored in the first period, with Kenzie Robinson and Bell adding markers in the final frame to lift the Wildcats (2-0) to a 3-1 win over the Wild (0-3). Jenna Marshall made 11 saves for the Wildcats, who fired 61 at Norman goalie Shayna Moore.
